[Well, WPV continues to be isolated from environmental samples in multiple locations in Pakistan and Afghanistan, and cVDPV continues to circulate in Nigeria, as evidenced by a newly confirmed AFP case and positive environmental samples. Overall, 2018 has not been a "good year" for polio, with higher numbers (marginally) of WPV-associated cases and cVDPV associated cases. Hopefully, 2019 will be a better year.

For a map showing the locations of cases of WPV and cVDPV, see http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/.

